Before applyting any sort of preprocessing on data, just want to conduct Hypothesis to understand the impact of feature on target vairable. Because if I apply pd.dropna(), I lose 20% of data.

I ran a two-sided Kruskal Wallis test. Given our group standard deviations were not equal, I decided it was not appropriate to use an ANOVA.

Does INSPECTION_TYPE effects the NEXT_INSPECTION_GRADE_C_OR_BELOW ?

In [11]:
group_Routine_Inspection = data1[data1['INSPECTION_TYPE'] == 'Routine Inspection']['NEXT_INSPECTION_GRADE_C_OR_BELOW'].dropna()
group_Re_inspection = data1[data1['INSPECTION_TYPE'] == 'Re-inspection']['NEXT_INSPECTION_GRADE_C_OR_BELOW'].dropna()
group_Typical_Inspection = data1[data1['INSPECTION_TYPE'] == 'Typical Inspection']['NEXT_INSPECTION_GRADE_C_OR_BELOW'].dropna()

statistic, p_value = kruskal(group_Routine_Inspection,group_Re_inspection,group_Typical_Inspection)

print("p-value:", p_value)

alpha = 0.05
if p_value < alpha:
    print("Reject the null hypothesis: 'INSPECTION_TYPE' has a significant effect on 'NEXT_INSPECTION_GRADE_C_OR_BELOW.'")
else:
    print("Fail to reject the null hypothesis: 'INSPECTION_TYPE' does not have a significant effect on 'NEXT_INSPECTION_GRADE_C_OR_BELOW.'")

In [ ]:
grade_A = data4[data4['CURRENT_GRADE'] == 'A']['CURRENT_DEMERITS']
grade_B = data4[data4['CURRENT_GRADE'] == 'B']['CURRENT_DEMERITS']
grade_C = data4[data4['CURRENT_GRADE'] == 'C']['CURRENT_DEMERITS']

# Kruskal-Wallis test
statistic, p_value = kruskal(grade_A,grade_B,grade_C)

# alpha
alpha = 0.05

# Compare the p-value to aplha
if p_value < alpha:
    print("Reject the null hypothesis: 'CURRENT_GRADE' has a significant effect on 'CURRENT_DEMERITS.'")
else:
    print("Fail to reject the null hypothesis: 'CURRENT_GRADE' does not have a significant effect on 'CURRENT_DEMERITS.'")

Reject the null hypothesis: 'CURRENT_GRADE' has a significant effect on 'CURRENT_DEMERITS.'
